  "response": "To get a job at ISRO (Indian Space Research Organisation) as a B.Tech CSE graduate, follow these steps:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering\n- Minimum 65% aggregate marks\n- Age usually between 18-35 years\n\n2. Recruitment Channels:\n- ISRO Career Portal\n- Direct recruitment\n- ISRO Centralized Recruitment Project (ICRP)\n- Annual Recruitment Notifications\n- Walk-in interviews\n\n3. Exam Preparation:\n- Computer Science fundamentals\n- Programming languages (C, C++, Java)\n- Data structures and algorithms\n- Operating systems\n- Computer networks\n- Software engineering\n- Database management systems\n\n4. Skill Enhancement:\n- Learn Python\n- Machine learning\n- Artificial intelligence\n- Embedded systems\n- Knowledge of space technology\n- Strong mathematics background\n\n5. Competitive Exams:\n- GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering)\n- ISRO's own recruitment exam\n\n6. Additional Recommendations:\n- Internships in space/technology domains\n- Research publications\n- Participate in space technology workshops\n- Learn technical skills related to space technology\n\n7. Application Process:\n- Monitor ISRO official website\n- Prepare required documents\n- Apply through proper channels\n- Clear written test and interview",
